; DOMAIN: order-theory [CLOSED, derived 2026-07-24] ; Claim: every monotone map on a complete lattice has a complete lattice of fixed points (Knaster-Tarski). ; Structure: (complete-lattice L) (monotone f). ; Result: lfp(f)=inf{x | f(x)<=x}; gfp(f)=sup{x | x<=f(x)}; Fix(f) is itself a complete lattice. ; Minimal: monotone + complete-lattice => nonempty complete lattice of fixed points (no continuity needed). ; Bridge: strengthens genesis_fixpoint_domain — drops Scott-continuity, requires only monotonicity + completeness. (= (lfp $f) (inf (prefixed-points $f)))